<item>
            <title>[HBASE-7493] Refactor snapshotting tests so that all they all are exercised the same way.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7493</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently we have two flavors of snapshots &amp;#8211; offline and flush snapshots.  We may have a few more with different consistency policies and we should test all of them with the same basic correctness tests (see TestFlushSnapshotFromClient).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should refactor or use parameterized tests to make this easy. I prefer refactor, easier to follow and to test only what you want individually.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12625974">HBASE-7493</key>
            <summary>Refactor snapshotting tests so that all they all are exercised the same way.</summary>
